Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.13,0:02:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the Astronaut Training Course,\Nwe're all together for PE,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.43,0:02:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but everyone can choose their own subjects, so sometimes\NI have different classes than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, this sure is a large school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.65,0:02:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it? Getting around is a little rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.99,0:03:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look, Lion-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Fuchuuya, the annoying brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.25,0:03:08.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Kei-chan and Suzuki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that guy? He doesn't have eyebrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and that's Marika-chan over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.43,0:03:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Lion-san's intrigued by her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H... h-hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.70,0:03:45.03,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6\fs18\3c&HF7EAE0&\c&HF7EAE0&\frz0.9294\pos(654.22,8.7)\bord2\4c&HE0CAB9&}Lecture Room
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.70,0:03:45.03,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6\fs18\frz0.9294\pos(654.22,8.7)\bord0\4c&HE0CAB9&\4a&HFF&}Lecture Room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.41,0:03:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sano-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.66,0:03:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm? What do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and go to the classroom.\NClass will start soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sano-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.63,0:04:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say something to Asumi...\NI mean, to Kamogawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamogawa-san has been acting weird lately, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.40,0:04:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're not responding, does that mean\Nyou feel guilty about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.15,0:04:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're trying to ask, but I can't\Nrespond about something that I don't recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you coming to me about\NKamogawa in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Kamogawa say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.54,0:04:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asumi won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:45.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asumi isn't the kind of\Nperson who tells on people!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.43,0:04:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She keeps everything inside,\Nno matter what people say to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.85,0:04:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's Kei yelling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about the little seagull, perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, they all go on about\NKamogawa, Kamogawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.95,0:05:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I will respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine to worry about your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead of worrying about other people, why don't\Nyou worry about getting them out of the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't enough seats to allow everyone\Nto be friends and become astronauts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there was just one seat left,\Nwould you let Kamogawa take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.45,0:05:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the other courses, even if you don't\Nproceed into the space program,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.83,0:06:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you can receive other qualifications, and it's advantageous\Nfor employment and further education.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also one reason why so many\Npeople apply for this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, with the Astronaut Training Course,\Nthere's not much value if you don't go through with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew that from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one believes that everyone can go to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that Sano guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one person who believes\Nthat everyone can go to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.29,0:06:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no mistaking it. It's that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But if it's that girl, why is she in\Nthe same grade as the little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lion-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you worried about what\Nthat teacher said, little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that by looking at the cost of training,\Nand the number of rockets that are to be launched,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it will be impossible for everyone to\Ngo to space before they graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,John Glenn was 72 years old\Non his second space flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.76,0:07:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In 1962, he became the first American astronaut\Nto orbit the Earth as part of Project Mercury.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that as well, right, little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.31,0:07:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last year, a Russian cosmonaut celebrated his\Nbirthday on the International Space Station...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.15,0:07:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was his name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was pretty old as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However old you are, there is\Nstill a chance to go into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With you and everyone else being so young,\Nthere are still many opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.96,0:08:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lion-san, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.59,0:08:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go find a book on the\Nhistory of space at the library!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.88,0:08:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll definitely be able to go with everyone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There don't seem to be a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:09:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Kei-chan went...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're wondering about Oumi-san,\NI saw her at the cafeteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's probably planning to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strike?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just leave it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.87,0:10:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there are times when\Nyou just want a day to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.63,0:10:13.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now then, page 80 in your textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you go out to space in a rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.69,0:10:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,different forces act on the rocket\Nthan upon your return to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After taking off vertically, the shuttle turns\Nhorizontally in order to gain speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, when the spacecraft re-enters\Nthe atmosphere upon returning to Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:11:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we use that resistance provided by\Nthe atmosphere to our advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.63,0:11:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The resistance in the atmosphere helps to\Nlower the speed without expending fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.19,0:11:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is troublesome, Sano-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are complaints from the\Nstudents' parents as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.15,0:11:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Getting them out of the way..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And worse, this is at a time when people are\Ncomplaining about the strength training!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't say things to lower the\Nstudents' motivations any further!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.21,0:11:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do not recall saying anything strange.\NThe truth is the truth, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you say that, it's a fact that there\Nare students boycotting your class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.67,0:11:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something is wrong with\Nyour attitude these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are even rumors going on\Nabout you between the teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.43,0:11:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head teacher is planning disciplinary action...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:52.31,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,0)\\bord0\fnSquare 721 Blk\frx30\fry358\pos(441.94,339.2)\frz160.5\blur0.8}Space Physics
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already submitted my resignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sano-sensei! I didn't mean\Nto have you go that far...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.79,0:12:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.96,0:12:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wondering why you had\Nsuch a problem with Kamogawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.35,0:12:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt bad, but I looked into it a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were in the JAMSF Shishigou\NDevelopment Team, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.73,0:12:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you and Kamogawa's\Nfather there at the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.99,0:12:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That really was an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was not just an accident,\Nit was a willful disaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:13:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is true that Kamogawa Tomorou\Nand I were there at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my work was scrapped because\Nhe wanted safety first!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My design that I had worked on for years...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because he was liked by the team leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.73,0:13:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had no right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.69,0:13:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then that happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Decades after that accident, at every\Nopportunity, people would say...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"So, you were part of the death team?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.29,0:13:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I was taken off the\Nteam and couldn't do anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.42,0:13:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were a participant in that\Nbig mistake, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was thoughtless of me to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't ask you for anything again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everywhere I go, that\Nabominable incident follows me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you chose Kamogawa Asumi\Nbecause of her eyes, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.36,0:14:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those eyes... what was it about those eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.78,0:14:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that man hadn't taken\Neverything away from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that's enough misguided resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after you were dropped from the team,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamogawa Tomorou was dropped from\Nthe Shishigou Development Team as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That can't be possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really know the details myself,\Nbut I heard an unsettling rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:40.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rumor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as Kamogawa was\Ndropped from the team,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.27,0:14:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the budget for the Shishigou\Nwas drastically reduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shishigou, famous for being all-Japanese...\Nwasn't actually made entirely within this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:15:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason behind the accident\Nis still a state secret, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Marika-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.14,0:15:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, where's Kei-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.56,0:15:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead of entering the campus,\Nshe made a U-turn and ran off somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.86,0:15:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.65,0:15:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it because first period is Sano-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.13,0:15:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really... we always have to\Ntake care of that dummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found you, Kei-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Class is going to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:15:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.69,0:16:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't go to Space Physics\Nyesterday either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you drop this credit,\Nwe can't graduate together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't ever want to take lessons\Nfrom Sano-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were told all that, but\Nyou don't feel anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't think he was a teacher\Nthat would say those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with caring for your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.58,0:16:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be a person who\Ncan't treasure her friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.25,0:16:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kei-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.55,0:16:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't say anything back to that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Marika-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.23,0:16:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pathetic because\NI couldn't say anything back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's frustrating!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be too late to tell him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.40,0:16:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go because\NI can't think of what to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't have to say anything back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.66,0:17:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's just go to class, okay, Kei-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.45,0:17:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So are you coming to class, or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.33,0:17:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, it's going to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it! You want me to go to class, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For crying out loud, why did it turn out this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.60,0:17:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's got such a happy face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.10,0:17:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The little seagull's smile sure is cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.19,0:17:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could that stupid look...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trying too hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dammit, everyone around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.78,0:17:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here he comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be teaching this for a while, starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Shiomi. Nice to meet you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.25,0:17:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.46,0:17:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Sano-sensei... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:18:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sano-sensei has decided to leave the school\Nfor a while, for his own reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.64,0:18:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Does that mean he quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.85,0:18:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, to put it simply, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.23,0:18:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is one thing I'd like to get\Nout of the way to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.28,0:18:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Astronaut Training Course has just been established,\Nso explanations may have been lacking
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and facilities might not have been\Nup to shape, so I apologize for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.71,0:18:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, it's true that it isn't possible for everyone\Nto go to space by the time they graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is also a fact that very few\Npeople will probably be able to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.01,0:18:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't want you to be pessimistic about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the near future, the use for\Nastronauts will surely increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that time comes, the fact that you have graduated\Nfrom this school will put you at an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.94,0:18:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many things may happen, but no matter\Nwhat sort of situation you are put in,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,do not throw away your vision and dreams of\Ngoing to space until the end and do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what the teaching staff\Nwishes from their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.91,0:19:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, we will proceed with the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.76,0:19:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, I wonder why he\Nsuddenly decided to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, of course he did, after those thoughtless\Nremarks in front of the students!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't quit over just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.43,0:19:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something else important must have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this "something?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cares what it is?\NIt's probably something stupid anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those eyes were scary anyway.\NI had no idea what he was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.16,0:19:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, and plus, listen to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.58,0:19:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That teacher said that Asumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\pos(419.429,220)\fnArabolical\c&H313837&\blur0.8}Professor's Room
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\pos(414.857,343.428)\fnSquare721 BT\blur0.8}Sano
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.78,0:21:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sano-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, it's the same for you, isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.39,0:21:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were looking at the same thing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.53,0:21:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There certainly was a time like that for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before I knew it, I couldn't see it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.21,0:21:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't lose sight of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.47,0:22:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why do adults have those sad expressions?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.81,0:22:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even Suzunari-sensei... even Lion-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.40,0:22:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.23,0:22:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even Sano-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.45,0:22:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only everyone could go into space...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm sure you'll be able to see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.38,0:22:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to see it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.46,0:22:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.02,0:22:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Ending}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.48,0:23:11.36,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}Look up at the stars in the night
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.66,0:23:23.92,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}The little stars, with their little lights
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.92,0:23:37.22,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}Are singing of humble happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.22,0:23:50.78,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}Look up at the stars in the night
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.78,0:24:03.75,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}Just like us, the stars without names
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.75,0:24:20.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\blur2}Are praying for humble happiness
